      "content": "hey so im prepping for this uni debate competition and my topic is about controversial urban planning policies in the mid-20th century. specifically i have to argue the 'pro' side for why redlining and certain types of zoning laws might have been seen as economically beneficial or necessary at the time, even if they're viewed negatively now. can u help me out and act as a devil's advocate? i need some really strong, structured points for the affirmative side so i can build my rebuttal. like, what would be the most logical economic or 'stability' based arguments for those policies?",
